This task implements Express REST API routes for card CRUD operations on a kanban board server. The server uses Express + better-sqlite3 + WebSocket broadcasts. After exploring the codebase, **all implementation files already exist and appear complete**. The agent must verify correctness by running tests and, if any tests fail, use the complete reference implementations below to create or fix the files.

**Test runner:** Node.js built-in `node --test` (not Jest/Mocha).
**HTTP testing:** `supertest`.
**DB:** `better-sqlite3` via `server/db/queries.js`, initialized with `initDb(':memory:')` for tests.

---

## Critical Files

| File | Role |
|------|------|
| `server/api/cards.js` | Express router — primary implementation target |
| `server/api/cards.test.js` | Supertest integration tests (`npm run test:integration`) |
| `server/test/cards.test.mjs` | Broader integration tests incl. WS broadcasts (`npm test`) |
| `server/index.js` | App factory `createApp()`, mounts routers at `/api`, error handler |
| `server/db/queries.js` | DB functions: `getCards`, `createCard`, `updateCard`, `deleteCard`, `moveCard`, `NotFoundError` |
| `server/package.json` | Test scripts |

**Test script reference (from `server/package.json`):**
```
npm run test:integration  →  node --test api/cards.test.js         (19 tests)
npm test                  →  node --test test/*.test.mjs            (does NOT include api/cards.test.js)
npm run test:all          →  node --test test/*.test.mjs db/queries.test.js api/cards.test.js  (ALL tests)
npm run test:coverage     →  same as test:all + c8 coverage check (≥70% lines, ≥80% functions)
```

---

## TDD Execution Plan

### Subtask 1 — Basic CRUD Endpoints

**Test cases to verify** (in `server/api/cards.test.js`):

| Test name | Expected behaviour |
|-----------|-------------------|
| `(1st) returns 200 with an empty array when no cards exist` | `GET /api/cards` → 200 + `[]` |
| `(2nd) returns 200 with Content-Type application/json` | `GET /api/cards` → `content-type: application/json` |
| `(3rd) returns card with comments array after createCard()` | After DB insert, `GET /api/cards` returns array where each card has a `comments` array |
| `returns 201 with created card on valid request` | `POST /api/cards {title:'My Card'}` → 201 |
| `response body has all required fields` | POST response includes `id, title, assignee, column, position, description, created_at` |
| `returns 200 with updated card` | `PATCH /api/cards/:id {title:'Updated'}` → 200 + updated title |
| `returns 204 on successful deletion` | `DELETE /api/cards/:id` → 204 |
| `204 response has no body (empty text)` | DELETE response body is empty string |

**Run:**
```bash
cd server && npm run test:integration
```

**Reference implementation — `server/api/cards.js`** (create/overwrite if missing or broken):

```js
import { Router } from 'express';
import { getCards, createCard, updateCard, deleteCard, moveCard, NotFoundError } from '../db/queries.js';
import { broadcast } from '../ws/broadcaster.js';

const router = Router();

// GET /api/cards — returns all cards, each with a nested `comments` array
router.get('/cards', (_req, res, next) => {
  try {
    const cards = getCards();
    return res.status(200).json(cards);
  } catch (err) {
    next(err);
  }
});

// POST /api/cards — requires `title`; returns 201 + created card
router.post('/cards', (req, res, next) => {
  const { title, assignee, column, description } = req.body ?? {};
  if (!title) {
    return res.status(400).json({ error: 'title is required' });
  }
  try {
    const card = createCard({ title, assignee, column, description });
    try { broadcast('card:created', card); } catch { /* isolate broadcast errors */ }
    return res.status(201).json(card);
  } catch (err) {
    next(err);
  }
});

// PATCH /api/cards/:id — updates allowed fields; 404 if card not found
const CARD_UPDATE_ALLOWED = ['title', 'assignee', 'column', 'description', 'position'];
router.patch('/cards/:id', (req, res, next) => {
  const updateData = req.body ?? {};
  try {
    const card = updateCard(req.params.id, updateData);
    // Only broadcast when at least one recognised field was sent (i.e. a DB write occurred)
    if (Object.keys(updateData).some(k => CARD_UPDATE_ALLOWED.includes(k))) {
      try { broadcast('card:updated', card); } catch { /* isolate broadcast errors */ }
    }
    return res.status(200).json(card);
  } catch (err) {
    if (err instanceof NotFoundError) {
      return res.status(404).json({ error: err.message });
    }
    next(err);
  }
});

// DELETE /api/cards/:id — 204 on success, 404 if not found
router.delete('/cards/:id', (req, res, next) => {
  try {
    deleteCard(req.params.id);
    try { broadcast('card:deleted', { id: req.params.id }); } catch { /* isolate */ }
    return res.status(204).send();
  } catch (err) {
    if (err instanceof NotFoundError) {
      return res.status(404).json({ error: err.message });
    }
    next(err);
  }
});

// PATCH /api/cards/:id/move — requires `column` and `position` (position:0 is valid)
router.patch('/cards/:id/move', (req, res, next) => {
  const { column, position } = req.body ?? {};
  if (!column || position === undefined || position === null) {
    return res.status(400).json({ error: 'column and position are required' });
  }
  try {
    const card = moveCard(req.params.id, column, position);
    try { broadcast('card:moved', card); } catch { /* isolate */ }
    return res.status(200).json(card);
  } catch (err) {
    if (err instanceof NotFoundError) {
      return res.status(404).json({ error: err.message });
    }
    next(err);
  }
});

export default router;
```

**Key architectural points:**
- `getCards()` returns cards with a nested `comments` array already — no extra mapping needed.
- `broadcast()` is always wrapped in its own `try-catch` so broadcast errors never affect HTTP responses.
- `export default router` (ESM, not CommonJS).

---

### Subtask 2 — Input Validation Middleware

**Test cases to verify** (in `server/api/cards.test.js`):

| Test name | Expected behaviour |
|-----------|-------------------|
| `returns 400 when title is missing` | `POST /api/cards {}` → 400 |
| `400 response body has an error string field` | POST 400 body → `{ error: string }` |
| `returns 400 when column is missing from body` | `PATCH .../move {position:0}` → 400 |
| `returns 400 when position is missing from body` | `PATCH .../move {column:'done'}` → 400 |
| `position: 0 is valid (move to first) — returns 200` | `PATCH .../move {column:'done', position:0}` → 200 |

**Validation rules (manual, no `express-validator`):**

- `POST /api/cards`: `if (!title)` — 400 + `{ error: 'title is required' }`
- `PATCH /api/cards/:id/move`: `if (!column || position === undefined || position === null)` — 400 + `{ error: 'column and position are required' }`. Use strict `=== undefined || === null` (NOT `!position`) so that `position: 0` remains valid.
- `PATCH /api/cards/:id`: No explicit body validation; existence check is handled by `updateCard()` throwing `NotFoundError`.

**Run:**
```bash
cd server && npm run test:integration
```

---

### Subtask 3 — Database Integration

**Test cases to verify** (in `server/api/cards.test.js`):

| Test name | Expected behaviour |
|-----------|-------------------|
| `(3rd) returns card with comments array after createCard()` | DB card appears in GET with `comments: []` |
| `returns 201 with created card on valid request` | POST → card persisted and returned |
| `returns 200 with updated card` | PATCH → updateCard writes to DB, response reflects change |
| `returns 204 on successful deletion` | DELETE → deleteCard removes from DB |

**Integration pattern:**
- Tests call `initDb(':memory:')` in `before()` and `closeDb()` in `after()`. The app is created with `createApp()` (which does NOT call `initDb` — DB lifecycle is external to the app factory).
- `beforeEach` in PATCH and DELETE suites calls `createCard()` directly (bypassing HTTP) to set up test data.
- The import in `server/api/cards.js` must be:
  ```js
  import { getCards, createCard, updateCard, deleteCard, moveCard, NotFoundError }
    from '../db/queries.js';
  ```
  Path is relative from `server/api/` to `server/db/`.

**Run:**
```bash
cd server && npm run test:all
```

---

### Subtask 4 — Comprehensive Error Responses with HTTP Status Codes

**Test cases to verify** (in `server/api/cards.test.js`):

| Test name | Expected behaviour |
|-----------|-------------------|
| `returns 404 when card not found` (PATCH) | `PATCH /api/cards/no-such-id` → 404 |
| `404 response body has an error string field` (PATCH) | PATCH 404 body → `{ error: string }` |
| `returns 404 when card not found` (DELETE) | `DELETE /api/cards/no-such-id` → 404 |
| `returns 404 when card not found` (move) | `PATCH /api/cards/no-such-id/move` → 404 |

**HTTP status code contract:**
- `400` — Missing required fields (title for POST; column/position for PATCH move). Returned inline, before any DB call.
- `404` — Card not found. `updateCard()` and `deleteCard()` throw `NotFoundError` when `changes === 0`; `moveCard()` throws `NotFoundError` when card lookup returns nothing. Catch and return `res.status(404).json({ error: err.message })`.
- `500` — Any other unhandled error. Call `next(err)` to reach Express error handler in `server/index.js`:
  ```js
  app.use((err, _req, res, _next) => {
    const status = err.status || err.statusCode || 500;
    res.status(status).json({ error: err.message || 'Internal Server Error' });
  });
  ```

**Router mounting in `server/index.js`** (must already exist):
```js
import cardsRouter from './api/cards.js';
// ...
app.use('/api', cardsRouter);
```

**Run:**
```bash
cd server && npm run test:all
```

---

## Execution Order (Agent Steps)

1. **Read existing files** to confirm they exist and match the reference implementations above.

2. **Run integration tests** (fast feedback):
   ```bash
   cd server && npm run test:integration
   ```
   All 19 tests in `api/cards.test.js` must pass.

3. **Run full test suite:**
   ```bash
   cd server && npm run test:all
   ```
   All tests in `api/cards.test.js` AND `test/cards.test.mjs` must pass.

4. **If any test fails:**
   a. Read the exact failure message.
   b. Locate the failing test case in the test file.
   c. Compare the behaviour against the reference implementations in this plan.
   d. Fix only the code that causes the failure — do not remove existing passing tests.
   e. Re-run `npm run test:all` to confirm green.

5. **Run coverage check:**
   ```bash
   cd server && npm run test:coverage
   ```
   Must meet thresholds: ≥70% lines, ≥80% functions.

---

## Verification

```bash
# Primary verification — all integration tests
cd server && npm run test:all

# Coverage check
cd server && npm run test:coverage
```

**Expected passing test counts:**

| File | Suite | Tests |
|------|-------|-------|
| `api/cards.test.js` | GET /api/cards | 3 |
| `api/cards.test.js` | POST /api/cards | 4 |
| `api/cards.test.js` | PATCH /api/cards/:id | 3 |
| `api/cards.test.js` | DELETE /api/cards/:id | 3 |
| `api/cards.test.js` | PATCH /api/cards/:id/move | 6 |
| `test/cards.test.mjs` | POST /api/cards (with WS) | 6 |
| `test/cards.test.mjs` | PATCH /api/cards/:id (with WS) | 7 |
| `test/cards.test.mjs` | DELETE /api/cards/:id (with WS) | 7 |
| `test/cards.test.mjs` | PATCH /api/cards/:id/move (with WS) | 8 |

All tests green = task complete.

